er{:id 951325, :key "journals/jacm/Phuong76", :title "Solution of Integer Programs with a Quadratic Objective Function.", :abstract "This paper presents a branch and bound method for solving problems in which the objective function is quadratic, the constraints are linear, and some or all variables are required to be integer. The algorithm is obtained by grafting an inverse-basis version of Beale's method onto the Land-Doig procedure. The code has been tested on a computer, and computational results with various strategies of branching are reported.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 707016, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Ta Huu Phuong"}), :year 1976, :venue "J. ACM", :ncit 0, :string "Solution of Integer Programs with a Quadratic Objective Function.. This paper presents a branch and bound method for solving problems in which the objective function is quadratic, the constraints are linear, and some or all variables are required to be integer. The algorithm is obtained by grafting an inverse-basis version of Beale's method onto the Land-Doig procedure. The code has been tested on a computer, and computational results with various strategies of branching are reported.", :doc-id "Solution of Integer Programs with a Quadratic Objective Function. 1976  "}, 838877 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 838877, :key "journals/dam/ScozzariT08", :title "A clique algorithm for standard quadratic programming.", :abstract "A standard Quadratic Programming problem (StQP) consists in minimizing a (nonconvex) quadratic form over the standard simplex. For solving a StQP we present an exact and a heuristic algorithm, that are based on new theoretical results for quadratic and convex optimization problems. With these results a StQP is reduced to a constrained nonlinear minimum weight clique problem in an associated graph. Such a clique problem, which does not seem to have been studied before, is then solved with an exact and a heuristic algorithm. Some computational experience shows that our algorithms are able to solve StQP problems of at least one order of magnitude larger than those reported in the literature.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 872059, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Andrea Scozzari"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 831734, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Fabio Tardella"}), :year 2008, :venue "Discrete Applied Mathematics", :ncit 11, :string "A clique algorithm for standard quadratic programming.. A standard Quadratic Programming problem (StQP) consists in minimizing a (nonconvex) quadratic form over the standard simplex. For solving a StQP we present an exact and a heuristic algorithm, that are based on new theoretical results for quadratic and convex optimization problems. With these results a StQP is reduced to a constrained nonlinear minimum weight clique problem in an associated graph. Such a clique problem, which does not seem to have been studied before, is then solved with an exact and a heuristic algorithm. Some computational experience shows that our algorithms are able to solve StQP problems of at least one order of magnitude larger than those reported in the literature.", :doc-id "A clique algorithm for standard quadratic programming. 2008  ,  "}, 1014301 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1014301, :key "journals/mp/Vavasis92a", :title "Approximation algorithms for indefinite quadratic programming.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 793748, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Stephen A. Vavasis"}), :year 1992, :venue "Math. Program.", :ncit 64, :string "Approximation algorithms for indefinite quadratic programming.. ", :doc-id "Approximation algorithms for indefinite quadratic programming. 1992  "}, 972862 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 972862, :key "journals/jcss/Ritter67a", :title "A Decomposition Method for Structured Quadratic Programming Problems.", :abstract "This paper describes a decomposition method for large structured quadratic maximization problems. The method can be applied to problems which contain coupling constraints or coupling variables occurring in the objective function.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 546093, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Klaus Ritter"}), :year 1967, :venue "J. Comput. Syst. Sci.", :ncit 3, :string "A Decomposition Method for Structured Quadratic Programming Problems.. This paper describes a decomposition method for large structured quadratic maximization problems. The method can be applied to problems which contain coupling constraints or coupling variables occurring in the objective function.", :doc-id "A Decomposition Method for Structured Quadratic Programming Problems. 1967  "}, 3130558 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3130558, :key "journals/automatica/GuptaBN11", :title "A novel approach to multiparametric quadratic programming.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 140650, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Arun Gupta"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 14153099, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Sharad Bhartiya"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 188075, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "P. S. V. Nataraj"}), :year 2011, :venue "Automatica", :ncit 3, :string "A novel approach to multiparametric quadratic programming.. ", :doc-id "A novel approach to multiparametric quadratic programming. 2011  ,  ,  "}, 3552447 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3552447, :key "journals/mp/Anstreicher12", :title "On convex relaxations for quadratically constrained quadratic programming.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1013219, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Kurt M. Anstreicher"}), :year 2012, :venue "Math. Program.", :ncit 7, :string "On convex relaxations for quadratically constrained quadratic programming.. ", :doc-id "On convex relaxations for quadratically constrained quadratic programming. 2012  "}, 3614367 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3614367, :key "journals/coap/BillionnetEL13", :title "An efficient compact quadratic convex reformulation for general integer quadratic programs.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 423520, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Alain Billionnet"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 739090, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Sourour Elloumi"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 14220203, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Amélie Lambert"}), :year 2013, :venue "Comp. Opt. and Appl.", :ncit 0, :string "An efficient compact quadratic convex reformulation for general integer quadratic programs.. ", :doc-id "An efficient compact quadratic convex reformulation for general integer quadratic programs. 2013  ,  ,  "}, 1014463 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1014463, :key "journals/mp/BillionnetE07", :title "Using a Mixed Integer Quadratic Programming Solver for the Unconstrained Quadratic 0-1 Problem.", :abstract "In this paper, we consider problem (P) of minimizing a quadratic function q(x)=x tQx+ctx of binary variables. Our main idea is to use the recent Mixed Integer Quadratic Programming (MIQP) solvers. But, for this, we have to first convexify the objective function q(x). A classical trick is to raise up the diagonal entries of Q by a vector u until (Q+diag(u)) is positive semidefinite. Then, using the fact that xi2=xi, we can obtain an equivalent convex objective function, which can then be handled by an MIQP solver. Hence, computing a suitable vector u constitutes a preprocessing phase in this exact solution method. We devise two different preprocessing methods. The first one is straightforward and consists in computing the smallest eigenvalue of Q. In the second method, vector u is obtained once a classical SDP relaxation of (P) is solved.We carry out computational tests using the generator of (Pardalos and Rodgers, 1990) and we compare our two solution methods to several other exact solution methods. Furthermore, we report computational results for the max-cut problem.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 423520, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Alain Billionnet"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 739090, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Sourour Elloumi"}), :year 2007, :venue "Math. Program.", :ncit 77, :string "Using a Mixed Integer Quadratic Programming Solver for the Unconstrained Quadratic 0-1 Problem.. In this paper, we consider problem (P) of minimizing a quadratic function q(x)=x tQx+ctx of binary variables. Our main idea is to use the recent Mixed Integer Quadratic Programming (MIQP) solvers. But, for this, we have to first convexify the objective function q(x). A classical trick is to raise up the diagonal entries of Q by a vector u until (Q+diag(u)) is positive semidefinite. Then, using the fact that xi2=xi, we can obtain an equivalent convex objective function, which can then be handled by an MIQP solver. Hence, computing a suitable vector u constitutes a preprocessing phase in this exact solution method. We devise two different preprocessing methods. The first one is straightforward and consists in computing the smallest eigenvalue of Q. In the second method, vector u is obtained once a classical SDP relaxation of (P) is solved.We carry out computational tests using the generator of (Pardalos and Rodgers, 1990) and we compare our two solution methods to several other exact solution methods. Furthermore, we report computational results for the max-cut problem.", :doc-id "Using a Mixed Integer Quadratic Programming Solver for the Unconstrained Quadratic 0-1 Problem. 2007  ,  "}, 3547007 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3547007, :key "journals/corr/abs-1210-3684", :title "Heuristic algorithms for the bipartite unconstrained 0-1 quadratic programming problem", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1055555, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Daniel Karapetyan"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 123056, :fi